    • Method Detail

      • expr2function

        public Function expr2function(FunctionFactory factory,
                              Expression expr)
                       throws PrismException
        Transform PRISM expression to rational function. If successful, a function representing the given expression will be constructed. This is however not always possible, as not each PRISM expression can be represented as a rational function. In this case a PrismException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        factory - function factory used to construct function
        expr - PRISM expression to transform to rational function
        Returns:
        rational function representing the given PRISM expression
        Throws:
        PrismException - thrown if expr cannot be represented as rational function

      • constructModel

        public ParamModel constructModel(ModelGeneratorSymbolic modelGenSym,
                                 java.lang.String[] paramNames,
                                 java.lang.String[] lowerStr,
                                 java.lang.String[] upperStr)
                          throws PrismException
        Construct a parametric model and return it. All of paramNames, lower, upper must have the same length, and lower bounds of parameters must not be higher than upper bounds.
        Parameters:
        modelGenSym - The ModelGeneratorSymbolic interface providing the model
        paramNames - names of parameters
        lowerStr - lower bounds of parameters
        upperStr - upper bounds of parameters
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • reserveMemoryAndExploreStates

        private void reserveMemoryAndExploreStates(ModelGeneratorSymbolic modelGenSym,
                                           ParamModel model,
                                           StateStorage<State> states)
                                    throws PrismException
        Reserves memory needed for parametric model and reserves necessary space. Afterwards, transition probabilities etc. can be added.
        Parameters:
        modulesFile - modules file of which to explore states
        model - model in which to reserve memory
        modelType - type of the model to construct
        engine - the engine used to compute state successors, etc.
        states - list of states to be filled by this method
        Throws:
        PrismException - thrown if problems in underlying methods occur

        Parameters:
        modulesFile - modules file of which to construct parametric model
        Returns:
        parametric model constructed
        Throws:
